Hi All. For todays product call, this is feedback from Natures Way on Fridays call: No interest in supply/production planning solution - farmers volatility is 100% manual; ie changes in quantity/ speed is done over phone with manual revised POs issued.
Little interest in logistics from CIO - unsurprisingly

BUT Demand Planning needs improving. They have looked several times at solutions to overlay Dynamics AX 2012. But never identified solution that could offer genuine value above current method (which is unclear; sounds like IBM Planning Analytics + XLS). They can potentially be interested in a 7B solution. But would be 2023 Purchase. Next step would be they would need us to identify where exactly we think we can add value to baseline.

Not really part of the scope of this doc, but we‚Äôll need to start defining some reports based on this. Ultimately, this links to product planning and prioritisation. See my point on feasible and credible roadmap.

Let‚Äôs start by playing by ear here. I think it‚Äôs just common sense. I definitely wouldn‚Äôt like 100 small tasks adding noise to the roadmap but don‚Äôt want too much bandwidth untracked. Ideally some of these tasks can also be planned (even quarters ahead)
